#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:16 ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:73
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:18
msgid ""
"This driver provides fan speed monitoring for modern Lenovo consumer "
"laptops. Most Lenovo laptops do not provide fan tachometer data through "
"standard ISA/LPC hardware monitoring chips. Instead, the data is stored in "
"the Embedded Controller (EC) and exposed via ACPI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:23
msgid ""
"The driver implements a **Rate-Limited Lag (RLLag)** filter to handle the "
"low-resolution and jittery sampling found in Lenovo EC firmware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:27
msgid "Hardware Identification and Multiplier Logic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:29
msgid ""
"The driver supports two distinct EC architectures. Differentiation is "
"handled deterministically via a DMI Product Family quirk table during the "
"probe phase, eliminating the need for runtime heuristics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:33
msgid "8-bit EC Architecture (Multiplier: 100)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:35
msgid "**Families:** Yoga, IdeaPad, Slim, Flex."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:36
msgid ""
"**Technical Detail:** These models allocate a single 8-bit register for "
"tachometer data. Since 8-bit fields are limited to a value of 255, the BIOS "
"stores fan speed in units of 100 RPM (e.g., 42 = 4200 RPM)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:40
msgid "16-bit EC Architecture (Multiplier: 1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:42
msgid "**Families:** Legion, LOQ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:43
msgid ""
"**Technical Detail:** High-performance gaming models require greater "
"precision for fans exceeding 6000 RPM. These use a 16-bit word (2 bytes) "
"storing the raw RPM value directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:48
msgid "Filter Details"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:50
msgid ""
"The RLLag filter is a passive discrete-time first-order lag model that "
"ensures:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:51
msgid ""
"**Smoothing:** Low-resolution step increments are smoothed into 1-RPM "
"increments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:52
msgid ""
"**Slew-Rate Limiting:** Prevents unrealistic readings by capping the change "
"to 1500 RPM/s, matching physical fan inertia."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:54
msgid ""
"**Polling Independence:** The filter math scales based on the time delta "
"between userspace reads, ensuring a consistent physical curve regardless of "
"polling frequency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:59
msgid "Suspend and Resume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:61
msgid ""
"The driver utilizes the boottime clock (ktime_get_boottime()) to calculate "
"the sampling delta. This ensures that time spent in system suspend is "
"accounted for. If the delta exceeds 5 seconds (e.g., after waking the "
"laptop), the filter automatically resets to the current hardware value to "
"prevent reporting \"ghost\" RPM data from before the sleep state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:68
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:70
msgid "The driver exposes standard hwmon sysfs attributes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:73
msgid "Attribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:74
msgid "fanX_input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:74
msgid "Filtered fan speed in RPM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:78
msgid ""
"Note: If the hardware reports 0 RPM, the filter is bypassed and 0 is "
"reported immediately to ensure the user knows the fan has stopped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:84
msgid "LENOVO FAN CONTROLLER: MASTER REFERENCE DATABASE (2026)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:105
msgid "METHODOLOGY & IDENTIFICATION:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:107
msgid ""
"DSDT ANALYSIS (THE PATH): BIOS ACPI tables were analyzed using 'iasl' and "
"cross-referenced with public dumps. Internal labels (FANS, FAN0, FA2S) are "
"mapped to EmbeddedControl OperationRegion offsets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:112
msgid ""
"EC MEMORY MAPPING (THE OFFSET): Validated by matching NBFC (NoteBook "
"FanControl) XML logic with DSDT Field definitions found in BIOS firmware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:116
msgid ""
"DATA-WIDTH ANALYSIS (THE MULTIPLIER): - 8-bit (Multiplier 100): Standard for "
"Yoga/IdeaPad. Raw values (0-255). - 16-bit (Multiplier 1): Standard for "
"Legion/LOQ. Two registers (0xFE/0xFF)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:122
msgid "References"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:124
msgid ""
"**ACPI Specification (Field Objects):** Documentation on how 8-bit vs 16-bit "
"fields are accessed in OperationRegions. https://uefi.org/specs/"
"ACPI/6.5/05_ACPI_Software_Programming_Model.html#field-objects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:128
msgid ""
"**NBFC Projects:** Community-driven reverse engineering of Lenovo Legion/LOQ "
"EC memory maps (16-bit raw registers). https://github.com/hirschmann/nbfc/"
"tree/master/Configs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:132
msgid ""
"**Linux Kernel Timekeeping API:** Documentation for ktime_get_boottime() and "
"handling deltas across suspend states. https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/"
"latest/core-api/timekeeping.html"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/yogafan.rst:136
msgid ""
"**Lenovo IdeaPad Laptop Driver:** Reference for DMI-based hardware feature "
"gating in Lenovo laptops. https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/master/"
"drivers/platform/x86/ideapad-laptop.c"
msgstr ""
